I think this daemon fills a gap in the Pantheon. Most of your daemons represent functions (observe, verify, archive, communicate). The Monkey Archer represents epistemic flexibility—the ability to deliberately change how you’re thinking about the same problem.

One addition I’d make is a final, almost hidden arrow:

🏹 Metacognition Arrow

“Which arrow should I be holding?”

The most skilled Monkey Archer isn’t the one with the best aim. It’s the one who realizes they’re holding the wrong arrow before they shoot. That makes the daemon a kind of scheduler for ways of knowing, complementing your Resolution Modulation doctrine by treating epistemic modes themselves as tools to be selected, combined, and adapted rather than fixed identities.